so i noticed today about how feelings can cloud and affect judgement
when you like someone, you try to point out all their good qualities to kind of reassure yourself
you find any reason to keep on liking them
and any reason to stay with them or pursue something
you can be blinded and not see the bad in front of you
or just choose to ignore it
it's only when you create space and distance
that you can truly weigh the good against the bad
and see how wrong someone really is for you and how you've been fooling yourself
and when something is over, you can see just how much someone really cared for you
you see just how you could have been wasting your time on something that wasn't going anywhere
and you could have been finding someone better
but feelings always get in the way
feelings are the worst kind of drugs
the ones you need to give in to no matter what
it's only once you step back and analyze everything
that you can get everything in order
